<pdd-reason>Exposes deterministic prompt and user-story ambiguity linting with an explicitly opted-in advisory LLM pass.</pdd-reason>

% Write `pdd/commands/prompt.py`, implementing the shared `prompt_lint` command used by `pdd checkup lint`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Implement a `prompt_lint` Click command (not a top-level `pdd prompt` group).
- Accept an optional prompt TARGET and optional `--stories <directory>`; require at least one.
- Run `scan_prompt` and `scan_stories` deterministically without network access.
- Support `--json` machine-readable output and `--strict` warning escalation.
- Accept `--ambiguity` for the deterministic ambiguity and observation checks.
- Accept `--llm` to enable advisory LLM-assisted ambiguity review on top of deterministic checks. Specifying `--llm` automatically enables `--ambiguity` checks. Without `--llm`, never invoke LLM or cloud-backed work.
- Explicitly document the read-only, advisory nature of the linter in the docstring and help texts.
- Preserve exit codes: 0 for clean, 1 for warnings, 2 for errors or strict warnings.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/prompt.py`
